car.Management

Class CarWash

  • java.lang.Object
    • car.Management.CarWash

  • public class CarWash
extends java.lang.Object

    Class description

    This class is purposed to hold the inventory of a simple car wash, disregarding the number of stands.

    Author:
    Razvan Radu

    • Constructor Detail

      • CarWash

        public CarWash()
        Default constructor, creating an empty instance.

    • Method Detail

      • openShop

        public void openShop()
        In case the car wash is closed, the method initializes the database to null. In case the car wash is already open with a previous call to the openShop method, a warning message is printed and the database is not reset.

      • washCar

        public void washCar()
        In case the car wash is open, the method adds the first car in the queue to the list of clients (cars that have been washed).

        In case the car wash is closed, an error message is printed, without stopping the execution.

      • standInLine

        public void standInLine(Car car)
        The standInLine method adds a car type to the washing queue.

        The permitted types are listed below. In case an illegal type is passed, an error message is printed.

        Parameters:
        car - A type of Car (Logan, Duster, Astra, Insignia)

      • closeShop

        public void closeShop()
        The closeShop method produces the freezing of the database.

      • getTodaysClients

        public java.util.List<Car> getTodaysClients()
        The getTodaysClients method returns an unique List of Car (Logan, Duster, Astra, Insignia) objects that have been marked as washed.

        The method can be called even if a closeShop method was not prior called.

      • getPostponedClients

        public java.util.List<Car> getPostponedClients()
        The getPostponedClients method returns an unique list of List of Car (Logan, Duster, Astra, Insignia) objects that have not yet been marked as washed.

        The method can be called even if a closeShop method was not prior called.

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
